@page "/airbrake"

<PageTitle>Air Brake (Z) Endorsement</PageTitle>

<Transition>
<div class="course-page airbrake">

  <section class="intro">
    <h1>Air Brake (Z) Endorsement Training</h1>
    <p>
      The <b>Air Brake (Z) Endorsement</b> is required for anyone operating vehicles equipped with air brake systems —  
      including <b>AZ and DZ commercial trucks</b>, buses, and other heavy-duty vehicles.
    </p>
    <p>
      This short but essential course provides the practical knowledge and hands-on training you need  
      to safely operate, inspect, and maintain air brake systems according to <b>Ontario Ministry of Transportation (MTO)</b> standards.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="overview">
    <h2>Course Overview</h2>
    <p>
      The Air Brake (Z) program includes both classroom instruction and practical in-yard training.  
      Completion of this course allows you to add the “Z” endorsement to your driver’s license.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Duration: 1 day (8 hours total)</li>
      <li>Official MTO-approved Air Brake Training</li>
      <li>Practical hands-on component using real trucks</li>
      <li>Written and practical tests completed on-site</li>
      <li>Certificate issued upon successful completion</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="training">
    <h2>What You’ll Learn</h2>
    <div class="facts">
      <div><b>Air Brake System Theory:</b> how air brakes work, components, and safety principles</div>
      <div><b>Air System Operation:</b> proper braking procedures, pressure checks, and warning devices</div>
      <div><b>Pre-Trip Inspection:</b> identifying defects, testing air loss, and governor cut-in / cut-out</div>
      <div><b>Hands-On Practice:</b> using our training truck to inspect and operate the system</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="requirements">
    <h2>Requirements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Valid Ontario driver’s license (any class)</li>
      <li>Minimum 16 years of age</li>
      <li>Basic English comprehension</li>
      <li>Ability to perform basic mechanical checks under instructor supervision</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="pricing">
    <h2>Program Options &amp; Tuition</h2>

    <div class="tier">
      <h3>Full Z Endorsement Course — <span>$400</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li>8-hour in-class + hands-on training</li>
        <li>Official written and practical tests included</li>
        <li>MTO-approved instructor and facility</li>
        <li>Certificate issued same day upon passing</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="note">Perfect for new AZ or DZ students who need to obtain the Z endorsement.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="tier premium">
      <h3>Refresher Air Brake Course — <span>$250</span></h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Half-day review and practice</li>
        <li>System troubleshooting and maintenance review</li>
        <li>Ideal for licensed drivers needing re-certification or confidence upgrade</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="note">Recommended for experienced drivers renewing or requalifying their Z endorsement.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq">
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Do I need the Z endorsement to drive a truck?</h3>
      <p>Yes. Any vehicle equipped with an air brake system requires a Z endorsement on your license.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Is the test included in the course?</h3>
      <p>Yes. Both written and practical tests are completed at our school on the same day.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How long is the certificate valid?</h3>
      <p>The Z endorsement remains valid as long as your driver’s license is valid — no separate renewal needed.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Can I take this course before AZ or DZ training?</h3>
      <p>Yes. We recommend completing the Z endorsement first — it’s required before starting AZ or DZ MELT training.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</div>
</Transition>
